$ Oracle SQL: RATIO_TO_REPORT (analytic function)
@ ratio_to_report

`ratio_to_report` is an → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/select/analytic that returns a value between 0 and 1 which indicates the weight of a numerical value in respect to the sum of all
numerical values in the same partition.

If multiplied by 100, the value of `ratio_to_report` can be interpreted as percentage. This is demonstrated in the following simple example:
gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/select/analytical_functions/ranking/ratio_to_report/spending.sql||

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/_examples/largest-reminder-method-for-rounding[Using the Largest Reminder Method to round percentages so that their sum is 100 percent]
